The paper discusses the challenges and requirements for Cyber-Physical Systems (CPS) and their resilience, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the integration of computing, communication, and control technologies, which suggests the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the monitoring and surveillance tasks, which could fall under software engineering (cs.SE) or networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of artificial intelligence (AI) in CPS, which could also be a potential sub-category.
